Ahead of the much anticipated local government election, the Oyo State Independent Electoral Commission (OYSIEC) yesterday released the timetable and guidelines for the conduct of election into the 33 councils. Commission Chairman Isiaka Olagunju in a statement appealed to the stakeholders to support and cooperate with the commission to enable it conduct a free, fair, credible and transparent election. He said prospective candidates are expected to obtain nomination forms in respect of the election at the commission’s headquarters on or before April 30. Olagunju added that the cost of nomination forms for candidates for the chairmanship position is N250,000, while those for the councillorship post is N100,000. He said: “In compliance with Section 30 Electoral Act 2010 (as amended), Section 5 (a) and Paragraph 1 (1) Schedule 2 of the State Independent Electoral Commission Law CAP 154, Laws of Oyo State of Nigeria 2000, the public is hereby informed that elections will be conducted in 33 local governments in Oyo State on May 15 between 8am and 3pm. “In the circumstance, prospective candidates are expected to obtain nomination forms in respect of the elections into their local governments at the commission’s headquarters at Quarters 484, Total Garden-Gate Road, Agodi GRA, Ibadan, Oyo State on or before April 30 upon payment of N250,000 only for the position of chairman or (B) N100,000 for the position of a councillor.”     